# Build context is the REPO ROOT (Dockerfile is backend/Dockerfile, context ".").
# This is the .dockerignore Docker actually honors — backend/.dockerignore is
# ignored for root-context builds. CRITICAL: keep .env out of the image (secrets
# must come from Secrets Manager at runtime, never baked in — a baked .env also
# leaks dev DB hosts/URLs that override the injected ones).
**/.env
**/.env.*
!**/.env.example

# Reinstalled inside the image; excluding speeds the build context massively.
**/node_modules
**/dist
**/build

# Not needed to build the backend image.
.git
.github
frontend
deploy
docs
**/__tests__
**/*.test.ts
**/*.spec.ts
**/coverage
*.log
*.md
.DS_Store
